= render_flash

.container
  %h1
    %strong
      Hello,
      = current_user.name
.container
  .row
    .col-sm-3.bg-success
      %h2
        = link_to @formulas_count.to_s + " Formulas", formulas_path
        = link_to "New Formula", new_formula_path, class: 'btn btn-success'
      %p Formula is the mixture of ingredients that form a diet for animals.
    .col-sm-3.bg-danger
      %h3
        = link_to @ingredients_count.to_s + " Ingredients", ingredients_path
        = link_to "New Ingredient", new_ingredient_path, class: 'btn btn-danger'
      %p An ingredient is a substance that forms part of a formula (in a general sense). For example, in cooking, recipes specify which ingredients are used to prepare a specific dish.
    .col-sm-3.bg-info
      %h3
        = link_to @nutrients_count.to_s + " Nutrients", nutrients_path
        = link_to "New Nutrient", new_nutrient_path, class: 'btn btn-info'
      %p Nutrients are the nutritious components in foods that an organism utilizes to survive and grow.

